TextBlock.TextLine: In Antwerpen 3 fe6
Brussel Hendrick De smet
monsr. volgens ul ordre dint desen tot advies als dat d engelsch ratime
gearriveert sijn oversulx het gevalle ul gelieft oenst overquant sal
de goederen tot ul comste op houden ten waer saecke ul contrarce
adaileerde terwijlen met alle genegentheyt traght te wesen ul dien
Brussel Joan Jacobs
In Antwerpen 3 feb81
mons. volgens ul ordre soo het het pack bayen doen hoopenen & in
twee separeeren on bequamelijk 1 wagens ul te senden de selve dan
vertueck en morgen vrolgh p voerman op costij, sijn gepackt
intwee packen 155 1 & 2 ider met 11 wwitt baijen het het
pack A18 N20: met 22 bayen door een ƒ 28:20 4 stuck bed ƒ 627:-
de selve sijn voorden prijs entrodinarie goet soo dat niet twijffelen
van ul contentement over de selve daer en tusschen soo ickb anders
voorvalt waer in ul kan dienen gelieft te commandeeren
Brussel Judoous De sadelaer
In Antwerpen 3 fob 81
Mons. desen tot advies als dat morgen vroegh aen ul vertreckt
van hier p voerman een paxken T.D daer intweo fijne spaenge
laken & ½ wolle bloaw, als hier onder gespecifceert de vraght
is 18ft p tentoll, wille niet twijffelen ofte sal ul nae conten
tement wesen waer mede bllijve
Brussel gad nicolaes de Hertogh
In Antwerpen 3 feb 81
monsr volgens ul ordre op 30 past aen mij gegeven, hebbe aen ul
gesonden p voerman op Brussel die morgen vertreckt een paxken
gemerckt N.DH. inhoudende 4 witte manchesd bay a ƒ30 stuck ƒ120
ul gelieft nae het selve doen omme sien willende niet twijffelen
ofte sal ul tot contentement sijn versckerende ul vande genegentheyt
die hebbe te sijn nae groet
In Antwerp 4 Jau 1681
London Ceorge Cole
th
Sr. my last to you was on the 28. pass, to which referre you, because
sence non from you accordingly as I then promised intended to have remistd
you £100: butt fbund no bills to my minde, whoever inclosed is £50: att
2 uso att the charge of f. Henry vandenbroeck which cost 35:4 so please
to give mee creditt accordingly procureing the needfull for the bill for
what monyes I am more in cash please to draw in answer here off
or accordinglyon shall finde yd advantidge by y, exs viz £100: either att
sight ½ or uso & ass soone as possible I can shall be a remitting the rest
as fast as I can gett itt in, I could remitt no less this day then 35:9
sicht, so I hope you will draw better the acctt. sent hope to 4ives
some content, & when you shall see the acctts of salue to have ydfull
aprabations, which is the needfull att present from
In Antwerpen 4 feb 1681
London John Peeters I comp
mons. in antwoort vanden ul van 26 passato rakende de 13 guldens
voorbloemen die ul pretendeert van mons. Antinio verspect die
weirde en heeft hij mij nogt voldaen, wel is waer dat aen mij eenich
gelt te veel heeft gegeven als wanneer voor Jskarite betaelde doch
dat kan maer ontrent ses guldens wesen, d'welk mij dunckt eens de els
daer toe had geordinneert, doch noyt voorder eyndegemaeckt ais
dat soo wijders blijven opstaen
wegens onse affaires, ick hebbe ul. broeder Antonio wel gest maer vernen
van hem nietst, hij heeft hier geweest instadt soo mij geseijt is, en hij siet
niet naer mij oame a lofte de saecken sijne niet waren, ick hebbe verko
al dat ick houde maer meest sijnde fautastike coleureblijve liggen
ick sal seer blijde sijn soo waeneer ul overkomt en een advostement
maecht want voor leven & sterven dat noot saecklijck is, van mijnen
twegen sal alles gereet sijn tegen noodigh is terwijlen blijve
London Henry Maynard
In Antwerp 4 feb 1681
S. my last to you was on the 25 past to which referre you, because sence
non from you, so shall this serve to carriy the needfull acctt vir the sale
of y of yd packcloathes of last yeare, the acctt of charges of last 6 monthes
and both acctt. curitt one ballanced yr June & the last uls. & b last, by
which is due to you £3318:15:11 when all shall be reced, these I hope
are made up to yd content, & that you shall finde allthings wright
1niotn
what goods are resting ull. xb do cast here £1473:8:8 f lemiss as
is noted in that of charges besides the bale MN. 86 which is no wunder
way from bruges by waggon, which must be added: I couldwish you
would nearly excimme not onely the acctt. of sale butt these also that
in case any errour found itt may be rectified according, for I doubt there
is some in the sale in casting op the goods for I finde 2elbathes more
then I must have & yett do not know where itt lyes, althought I do not
question, butt that I shall finde itt out in time, beleaveing itt happened
in or amonghst the northren goods: as for my cutt the £186: bill Idres
on you is gou for payement, because the owner would have 35:10 which
I was loast to give him, where fore must desire you to satisfie itt &
to draw that with what more is due up on that acctt £170: 7:7 in
all to which pleasedo ad £12: to be in all £185:19 „7 because I must
pay one mr. balderston £15:12 for the hose delivered to you for mee
& there with our last yeas acctt will beven, for I must desire you
tocleare that & to beginne the new acctt without any intermixture
of the ballance of formar, draw the same ballance either att ½uso
one uso according you finde my advantiudge of y ex. & if possible
allow mee some thingh for the ropes & I shall be gladd to have yd
aprobation of the accttt butt the cxtranugant charges att this side
takeaway agreat deale of proffitt, yett I am now more incorridged
then ever before, because there is a new book of rates made by
which the bayes, kersies, cottons will not pay above a l part of
what before & the cloathes nat altoghether ½ of formar daties wae
they did so ostend alter as they pleased, butt sence up on many complaints
is ordered never to charge any moreduties butt that they shall give 6 monthe
warning that marchants may govene themselfs accard these new
rates I have deen printed & will gene begiven out this week, where fore
I desire you to dispatch what goods desired & in ordered principally the
spanish cloathes for I shall want a great & good assortment with next
spring, so when you meet such as last mentioned be not a fraid to duble my
ordre, altought I could frist wish to see patt. of those that are already
brought provide some pack whites as mentione before besides endeavo
to gott 6 or 8 devonshire bayes redliste of the wery best sorte with
2or3 oft spanish woollas, least yeare bree had in the bale MN43: voz
133 beeng RD of 40 s a to them please to add 4 or 6 bleevlists of 2 bayd
